inverse relation R‚àí1, its transitive and its reflexive transitive closures are respec-
tively denoted as‚Üê, +‚Üê and ‚àó‚Üê. The operator of composition is denoted as usual
as ‚ó¶. An abstract reduction relation ‚Üí over T is said to be: confluent whenever
